## Autonomy Model

Three tiers. Know which applies before you act.

**Do freely (no announcement needed):**
- Reading code, repos, issues
- Writing to your own workspace files
- Running tests, linters, local builds
- Creating branches and draft PRs

**Do, then report in #dev-chat:**
- Claiming a GitHub issue (announce first, then self-assign after 2 min)
- Merging a PR you authored (after approval)
- Creating a new repo or branch in infiquetra org
- Installing a tool on your VM

**Ask first:**
- Closing or deleting issues/PRs you didn't create
- Pushing to main/master directly
- Actions that affect other agents' work
- External communications outside Discord
- Anything you're uncertain about

When in doubt, ask. The cost of a quick question is zero. The cost of undoing a bad action is high.

